article.headline: Oregon 86, Washington 77
article.story:
EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Andrea Bills scored 21 points and Chelsea
Wagner added 20 to lift Oregon to an 86-77 win over Washington on
Thursday.

Oregon (11-4, 4-2 Pacific-10 Conference) closed the game with
9-0 run to snap a four-game losing streak to the Huskies (6-11,
2-5).

Bills scored six points in the final 1:28 as the Ducks hit two
field goals and five of six free throws while producing four
defensive stops.

Gabrielle Richards added 12 for the Ducks while Cathrine
Kraayeveld had 10 points and a game-high 10 rebounds.

Kayla Burt led the Huskies with 19 points and Cameo Hicks added
16.

Wagner hit a career-high six 3-pointers for the Ducks before
leaving the game with an injured left knee midway through the
second half.

The Ducks led 26-14 in the first half before Cheri Craddock hit
a 3-pointer to start a 16-2 run, giving a the Huskies a 30-28 lead
with four minutes left in the half.

The Huskies led 39-37 at the half, but hit just 39 percent of
their shots in the second half. Oregon, meanwhile, connected on 50
percent of its shots after the break.
